Name: Investigate and fix the issue of multiple InvoiceOrder records being generated for the same Invoice.
Description: We have identified a recurring issue where multiple InvoiceOrder records are being created for a single Invoice. This behavior is unintended and can cause data inconsistencies in our system.The issue seems to involve two services:UpsertInvoice ServiceResponsible for updating or creating invoices.ConvertShopifyOrderToInvoiceOrder ServiceHandles the conversion of Shopify orders to InvoiceOrder records.It's possible that overlapping logic in these services or race conditions during execution are causing duplicate InvoiceOrder records to be created for the same Invoice.To replicate this issue, you may need to update the Shopify order multiple times. It seems that each update triggers actions in one or both services, possibly leading to the creation of duplicate InvoiceOrder entries.Update:-How to reproduce:Ensure an invoice already exists for the order.Verify that the shop's automatic invoice generation is enabled.Update the order, and immediately open the invoice corresponding to the updated order.Repeat this process multiple times to reproduce the issue.Conclusion: The issue arises when two UpsertInvoice services run simultaneously.One service is triggered by the user opening the invoice from the UI.The other is triggered by the Order Update webhook from shopify for the same invoice at the same time.These concurrent executions of the UpsertInvoice service lead to a race condition, causing the duplication of invoice_order records.
